<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMartindaleJones.2C_A.H.M..3B_Morris.2C_J.1992">Martindale, John R.; Jones, A.H.M.; Morris, J. (1992). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=fBImqkpzQPsC" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=fBImqkpzQPsC" rel="nofollow">The Prosopography of the Later Roman Empire</a></i>. <b>IIIa</b>. Cambridge University Press. pp.&#160;181-224. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521201608" class="internal">ISBN 0521201608</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=fBImqkpzQPsC" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=fBImqkpzQPsC" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=fBImqkpzQPsC</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Prosopography+of+the+Later+Roman+Empire&amp;rft.aulast=Martindale&amp;rft.aufirst=John+R.&amp;rft.au=Martindale%2C+John+R.&amp;rft.au=Jones%2C+A.H.M.%3B+Morris%2C+J.&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.volume=IIIa&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B181-224&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0521201608&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DfBImqkpzQPsC&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Belisarius"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>R. Boss, R. Chapman, P. Garriock, <i>Justinian's War: Belisarius, Narses and the Reconquest of the West</i>, Montvert Publications, 1993, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1874101019" class="internal">ISBN 1-874101-01-9</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Glanville_Downey&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Glanville Downey (page does not exist)">Glanville Downey</a>, <i>Belisarius,: Young general of Byzantium</i>, Dutton, 1960.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Percy_Stickney_Grant" title="Percy Stickney Grant">Percy Stickney Grant</a>, <i>The search of Belisarius;: A Byzantine legend</i>, Brentano's, 1907.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Edward_Gibbon" title="Edward Gibbon">Edward Gibbon</a> has much to say on Belisarius in <i><a href="/wiki/The_History_of_the_Decline_and_Fall_of_the_Roman_Empire" title="The History of the Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire">The History of the Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</a></i>, <a href="http://www.ccel.org/g/gibbon/decline/volume2/chap41.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ccel.org/g/gibbon/decline/volume2/chap41.htm" rel="nofollow">Chapter 41 online</a>.</li>
<li>Lord Mahon <a href="/wiki/Philip_Henry_Stanhope,_5th_Earl_Stanhope" title="Philip Henry Stanhope, 5th Earl Stanhope" class="mw-redirect">Philip Henry Stanhope, 5th Earl Stanhope</a>, <i>The Life of Belisarius</i>, 1848. Reprinted 2006 (unabridged with editorial comments) Evolution Publishing, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1889758671" class="internal">ISBN 1-889758-67-1</a>. <a href="http://www.evolpub.com/CRE/CREseries.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.evolpub.com/CRE/CREseries.html" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li>Lord Mahon <a href="/wiki/Philip_Henry_Stanhope,_5th_Earl_Stanhope" title="Philip Henry Stanhope, 5th Earl Stanhope" class="mw-redirect">Philip Henry Stanhope, 5th Earl Stanhope</a>, <i>The Life of Belisarius</i>, J. Murray, 1829. (1848 Second Edition, published without changes from the original edition.) With a new critical introduction and further reading by Jon Coulston. 2005 Westholme Publishing, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1594160198" class="internal">ISBN 1-59416-019-8</a> <a href="http://www.westholmepublishing.com/id35.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.westholmepublishing.com/id35.html" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Procopius" title="Procopius">Procopius</a>, <i>Belisarius and Narses</i>, Academic Fellowship, 1964.</li>
<li>Procopius, <i>The Secret History of the Court of Justinian</i>, <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/dirs/1/2/9/1/12916/12916-8.txt" class="external text" title="http://www.gutenberg.org/dirs/1/2/9/1/12916/12916-8.txt" rel="nofollow">online at Gutenberg Project</a>.</li>
</ul>
